
# Currency Converter

A simple currency converter application built with Python and Tkinter. This application allows you to convert between different currencies using real-time exchange rates.

## Features

- Convert between various currencies.
- Real-time exchange rate data from a public API.
- User-friendly graphical interface.
- Supports a wide range of currencies.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/currency-converter.git

a. Change the working directory to the project folder:

cd currency-converter

b. Install the required Python packages(make sure you have Python installed):

pip install requests

c. Run the application

python currency-converter.py

#Usage

Launch the application.

Select the source currency from the "From" dropdown menu.

Select the target currency from the "To" dropdown menu.

Enter the amount you want to convert in the input field.

Click the "Convert" button to see the converted amount.

#Dependencies

Python 3.x
Tkinter (usually included with Python)
requests

